45451.base_text:
You and I
Again and again
Always almost
Never enough.

variants.text:
You and I
Again and again
Always almost
Never enough.

45451.base_text:
See the rings pursue each other;
All below grows black as night,
Just as if mother
Had blown out the light!

variants.text:
See the rings pursue each other;
All below grows black as night,
Just as if mother
Had blown out the light!

45451.base_text:
But the dark pines of your mind dip deeper
And you are sinking, sinking, sleeper
In an elementary world;
There is something down there and you want it told.

variants.text:
But the dark pines of your mind dip deeper
And you are sinking, sinking, sleeper
In an elementary world;
There is something down there and you want it told.

45451.base_text: Than the gentleman above-named, there is nobody, in the whole circle of my acquaintance, whom I have more attentively studied, yet of whom I have less real knowledge, beneath the surface which it pleases him to present. …He will pass to the dark realm of Nothingness, but will not find me there.
They have no idea what happiness is. They don’t know that for us, without our love, there is neither happiness nor unhappiness: there is no life at all.

variants.text: They have no idea what happiness is. They don’t know that for us, without our love, there is neither happiness nor unhappiness: there is no life at all.

45451.base_text:
We two boys together clinging,
One the other never leaving

variants.text:
We two boys together clinging,
One the other never leaving

45451.base_text:
Patience, children, just a minute—
See the spreading circles die;
The stream and all in it
Will clear by-and-by.
